SIMPLE: croupier
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Croupier
<hw>Crou"pi*er</hw> <pr>(kr⟦oomac⟧"p⟦icr⟧*⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F.; prop., one who sits on the croup, and hence, in the second
place; an assistant. See 1st <er>Croup</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who presides at a gaming table and collects the stakes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who, at a public dinner party, sits at the lower
end of the table as assistant chairman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Croupous</ent>⟦br⟧
